  "raw_meta_yaml": "{% set version = \"0.15.2\" %}\n{% set python_min = \"3.10\" %}\n\npackage:\n  name: pygfx\n  version: {{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/p/pygfx/pygfx-{{ version }}.tar.gz\n  sha256: fdec0a4751443b68f6c484f70a56f31bfd84169c08d3701e037c9d586d4afe2b\n\nbuild:\n  noarch: python\n  script: \n    # The rendercanvas breakage was somewhat hard for a few people.\n    # However, i don't think it is worth constraining too much\n    # Remove the constraint on rendercanvas, let downstream project constrain themselves.\n    # https://github.com/pygfx/pygfx/commit/bf2d32983d44e5ddedd47df7edf0ebb33f8f9097\n    - sed -i.bak '/\"rendercanvas >=/d' pyproject.toml\n    - rm pyproject.toml.bak\n    - {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv\n  number: 0\n\nrequirements:\n  host:\n    - python {{ python_min }}\n    - pip\n    - setuptools\n    - flit-core\n  run:\n    - python >={{ python_min }}\n    - rendercanvas >=2.2\n    - numpy\n    - wgpu-py >=0.24.0,<0.28\n    - pylinalg >=0.6.8,<0.7.0\n    - freetype-py\n    - uharfbuzz\n    - jinja2\n    - hsluv >=5.0.0\n\ntest:\n  imports:\n    - pygfx\n  requires:\n    - python {{ python_min }}\n    - pip\n  commands:\n    - pip check\nabout:\n  home: https://github.com/pygfx/pygfx\n  summary: \"Pygfx' purpose is to bring powerful and reliable visualization to the Python world. 🚀\"\n  license: BSD-2-Clause\n  license_file: LICENSE\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - hmaarrfk\n",
